# Restart After Changes

After making **any code or configuration changes** to this project (Java, templates, CSS, application.properties, etc.), **restart the application** so changes take effect.

## What to do

1. **Stop** any process using port 8080 (e.g. existing Spring Boot instance).
2. **Start** the app again in the background: `mvn spring-boot:run -q` from the project root.

## Commands (PowerShell)

```powershell
cd d:\sarvsikshaai
$p = Get-NetTCPConnection -LocalPort 8080 -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Select-Object -ExpandProperty OwningProcess -Unique
if ($p) { Stop-Process -Id $p -Force }
mvn spring-boot:run -q
```

Run the last command (`mvn spring-boot:run -q`) in the **background** so the server keeps running.

Do **not** restart when the only edits were to documentation (e.g. README, PRIVACY_AND_LEGAL.md) or to this rule file.
